  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How does one score good marks in MAKAUT?",
  "response": "To score good marks in MAKAUT (Maulana Abul Kalam Azad University of Technology), formerly known as WBUT (West Bengal University of Technology), students can follow a few strategic steps:\n\n1. **Understand the Syllabus and Exam Pattern:**\n   - Get a clear understanding of the syllabus for each subject.\n   - Familiarize yourself with the examination pattern, including the types of questions asked.\n\n2. **Plan and Organize:**\n   - Create a study plan that allocates time for each subject.\n   - Organize your study materials, including textbooks, notes, and previous year question papers.\n\n3. **Attend Classes Regularly:**\n   - Attend all lectures and take notes.\n   - Engage in classroom discussions and clarify doubts with professors.\n\n4. **Consistent Study Routine:**\n   - Implement a daily study routine to stay consistent.\n   - Avoid last-minute cramming and focus on regular, steady study sessions.\n\n5. **Understand Concepts:**\n   - Focus on understanding the concepts rather than rote memorization.\n   - Use reference books, online resources, and tutorials for deeper understanding.\n\n6. **Practice Regularly:**\n   - Solve previous years' question papers and sample papers.\n   - Regular practice helps in time management and identifies important topics.\n\n7. **Revision:**\n   - Regularly revise topics you have covered to reinforce your memory.\n   - Use summaries, flashcards, and quick notes for effective revision.\n\n8. **Internal Assessments and Projects:**\n   - Participate actively in internal assessments, assignments, and projects.\n   - Prepare thoroughly for lab sessions and practicals, as they contribute to overall marks.\n\n9. **Group Study:**\n   - Engage in group study sessions to exchange knowledge and clear doubts.\n   - Discuss and solve complex problems with peers for better understanding.\n\n10. **Seek Help:**\n   - Reach out to professors, mentors, or tutors if you have difficulty understanding certain subjects.\n   - Utilize university resources like libraries and online portals for additional study materials.\n\n11. **Healthy Habits:**\n   - Maintain a healthy lifestyle with proper sleep, nutrition, and exercise.\n   - Avoid stress and take breaks to rejuvenate your mind.\n\nBy following these steps diligently, students can significantly improve their chances of scoring good marks in MAKAUT exams.",
